My visual data story

What do people usually describe dogs when they saw them?

From the plot, we can see that most participants tended to describe the behavior of the dogs they saw, followed by appearance and size.
This suggests that when people observe dogs, their actions are the first aspects that catch their attention.

How does the number of dogs vary by their size?

From this boxplot, we can see that small and medium dogs were the most frequently mentioned.
The spread is relatively wide, especially for medium-sized dogs. In contrast, large dogs are less frequently encountered.

Do people describe dogs differently depending on the time?

The chart shows that the length of descriptions fluctuates slightly across time, but most responses remain between 4 to 9 characters.
There is no strong upward or downward trend, but the loess line helps illustrate subtle variations.
It suggests that description style remains fairly consistent regardless of the time participants saw the dogs.
